title: SyntaxError: Missing Closing Parenthesis in index.js
root_cause_summary: The build failure is caused by a syntax error in the index.js file. Specifically, there is a missing closing parenthesis after the 'Hello there' string in the res.send() function call on line 6.
root_cause_detailed: The JavaScript interpreter encountered a SyntaxError while parsing the index.js file. This error occurs when the syntax of the code violates the rules of the JavaScript language. In this case, the error message 'missing ) after argument list' indicates that a function call is missing its closing parenthesis. The error is located on line 6 of index.js, where the res.send() function is called with the 'Hello there' argument.

fix_suggestions.title: Add missing closing parenthesis in index.js
fix_suggestions.description: This fix directly addresses the syntax error by adding the missing closing parenthesis to the res.send() function call.
implementation_steps: Step 2: Locate line 6 with the res.send() function call
Step 3: Add a closing parenthesis after the 'Hello there' string
Step 4: Save the file and commit the changes
fix_suggestions.source: Error message and syntax error analysis

fix_suggestions.title: Implement ESLint in the CI/CD pipeline
fix_suggestions.description: Adding a linter to the CI/CD pipeline will help catch syntax errors before deployment, preventing similar issues in the future.
implementation_steps: Step 1: Install ESLint in the project
Step 2: Configure ESLint with appropriate rules
Step 3: Add an ESLint step to the CI/CD workflow
Step 4: Update the workflow to fail if ESLint finds errors
fix_suggestions.source: Best practices for CI/CD and error prevention

fix_suggestions.title: Conduct a full code review of index.js
fix_suggestions.description: Performing a comprehensive code review of index.js may reveal other potential syntax errors or issues that could cause future failures.
implementation_steps: Step 1: Open index.js in a code editor
Step 2: Review each line of code for potential syntax errors
Step 3: Check for consistent coding style and best practices
Step 4: Make necessary corrections and improvements
Step 5: Have another developer review the changes

research_summary: Web research confirms that this type of SyntaxError is commonly caused by missing parentheses in function calls. The error message clearly indicates the nature of the problem, making it relatively straightforward to fix. Implementing a linter and conducting regular code reviews are recommended practices to prevent similar issues in the future.
